Philippine Police Warned Against Wanton Firing
MANILA , December 28 ( Xinhua ) -- Policemen found firing their guns to celebrate the new year will be fired , Roberto Lastimoso , chief of the Philippine National Police ( PNP ) , said here Monday .
Lastimoso said in a statement that there will be no mercy for policemen who fire their guns indiscriminately .
The Gunless Society of the Philippines has joined the campaign asking all gun holders to refrain from firing their firearms to celebrate the incoming year .
Private individuals who fire their guns will be charged in court and their license canceled .
Reynaldo Wycoco , PNP chief for the National Capital Region , has banned the firing of guns by policemen in Manila during the holiday season .
